div.p:
Suppoſe laſtly, wee are to adminiſter puniſhments for others, one puniſhment for all faults were not juſt: neither muſt wee puniſh in life, when a member would ſatisfie;

 nor in body, when goods are enough; nor in goods, when loſſe of credit is more then ſufficient; nor in much in any thing when a little would ſerv the turne: we muſt look with a charitable eye to both proportions,
               Proportio. 1 Arithmetica. 2 Geometrica. for we would be ſo done unto our ſelves.
